Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - Abstract This paper evaluates the stability properties of optimal monetary policy rules when professionals under adaptive learning have asymmetric preferences. The asymmetric preferences require volatility estimates in real time. An expectations-based rule can stabilize the economy, while a fundamentals-based rule leads to instability.
